You have to hold the switch down pretty hard. You’ve carefully swapped between every single finger barring your pinkies, trying to keep them from getting sore. You’ve thought of every possible way to hold down the switch, but the fact that it’s on the ceiling of the safe makes it impossible. Every joint in your body aches from the position you have to be in to keep holding the switch; you’re forced to be slumped down in order to fit your hand in the box.
